---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionReveal from '../../components/SectionReveal';
import IntelligenceLayerSpec from '../../components/IntelligenceLayerSpec';
import NewsletterForm from '../../components/NewsletterForm.astro';

const title = "The Context Field — The Operating Context That Holds Everything in Orbit";
const description = "The Context Field is the machine-readable operating context that pulls every AI tool, agent, and channel into coherent orbit. Six components. One shared foundation. Built for B2B SaaS companies scaling with AI.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebPage",
      "name": "The Context Field",
      "description": description,
      "url": "https://strategnik.com/physics-of-growth/context-field",
      "isPartOf": {
        "@type": "WebSite",
        "name": "Strategnik",
        "url": "https://strategnik.com"
      }
    })} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://strategnik.com" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Physics of Growth", "item": "https://strategnik.com/physics-of-growth" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Context Field", "item": "https://strategnik.com/physics-of-growth/context-field" }
      ]
    })} />
  </Fragment>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <a href="/physics-of-growth" class="text-small text-gray-400 hover:text-white mb-8 inline-block" data-animate-fade>
        &larr; Physics of Growth
      </a>
      <h1 class="text-display-lg mb-6" data-animate-hero>The Context Field</h1>
      <p class="text-body-lg text-gray-400" data-animate-hero-sub>
        Mass generates gravity. The Context Field is what that gravity actually is — the
        structured operating context that pulls every tool, agent, and channel into
        coherent orbit around the same center of mass.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="prose-minimal">

        <h2 data-animate>What the Context Field Is</h2>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.1">
          The Context Field is the machine-readable operating context — your brand spec,
          ICP hierarchy, competitive framing, content architecture, distribution schema,
          and measurement targets — encoded so every AI tool, every agent, and every
          team member works from the same shared foundation.
        </p>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.15">
          Think of it as the invisible force that gives structure to motion. Without it,
          your tools generate output in a vacuum. With it, every piece of content, every
          campaign, every agent action orbits the same strategic center.
        </p>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.2">
          This isn't a brand guidelines PDF that lives in a shared drive. It's
          infrastructure — structured, versioned, and designed to be consumed by machines
          as fluently as by humans.
        </p>

        <h2 data-animate>Why It Matters</h2>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.1">
          Without a context field, objects drift randomly. Your AI tools produce
          fragmented output. Your channels tell different stories. Your team starts
          from scratch every time. Every new hire, every new agency, every new tool
          gets a blank canvas instead of an operating system.
        </p>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.15">
          With a strong field, everything orbits the same center and moves in predictable,
          coherent paths. Content reinforces positioning. Agents generate on-brand output
          without babysitting. New team members ramp in days, not months. The field does
          the alignment work so people can do the thinking work.
        </p>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.2">
          The difference between companies that scale marketing cleanly and companies
          that fragment isn't talent or budget. It's whether the operating context exists
          and whether it's strong enough to hold everything in orbit.
        </p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Six Components -->
  <section class="section border-t border-gray-800">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="prose-minimal">
        <h2 data-animate>The Six Components</h2>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.1">
          The Intelligent Context Layer is built from six interlocking components. Each one
          encodes a different dimension of your go-to-market reality. Together, they
          form the complete operating context — managed and maintained through
          <a href="https://app.ontogent.ai" class="text-blue-bright hover:text-white transition-colors">Ontogent</a>,
          the platform for managing your Context Layer.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container-content" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <SectionReveal client:visible>
        <IntelligenceLayerSpec client:visible />
      </SectionReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Field Strength -->
  <section class="section border-t border-gray-800">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <div class="prose-minimal">

        <h2 data-animate>Field Strength Diagnostic</h2>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.1">
          A weak field means drift. A strong field means coherence. The question
          isn't whether you have a brand or a strategy — it's how well-specified and
          maintained your operating context actually is.
        </p>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.15">
          Most companies have fragments. A positioning doc from the last agency. An
          ICP slide from a board deck. Competitive intel scattered across Slack threads
          and sales call recordings. None of it encoded. None of it machine-readable.
          None of it maintained.
        </p>
        <p data-animate data-animate-delay="0.2">
          That's a weak field. And weak fields produce the symptoms everyone complains
          about: inconsistent messaging, off-brand AI output, slow ramp times, channels
          that contradict each other, and the persistent feeling that marketing is busy
          but not compounding.
        </p>

        <hr />

        <h2 data-animate>Diagnostic Questions</h2>
        <ul data-animate data-animate-delay="0.1">
          <li>If you gave an AI agent your brand context today, would it produce output you'd actually use?</li>
          <li>Can a new team member find and understand your ICP hierarchy, competitive positioning, and content strategy in one place?</li>
          <li>Are your measurement targets connected to your content architecture, or are they tracked in separate systems with separate definitions?</li>
          <li>When was the last time your competitive framing was updated? Does it reflect the market as it is now?</li>
          <li>Could you hand your operating context to a new agency and have them producing coherent work within a week?</li>
        </ul>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section border-t border-gray-800 text-center">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <SectionReveal client:visible>
        <h2 class="text-display-sm mb-4" data-animate>Measure Your Field Strength</h2>
        <p class="text-body-lg text-gray-400 mb-8" data-animate data-animate-delay="0.1">
          The Digital Context Audit maps your operating context across all six components and
          delivers the gap analysis, the architecture blueprint, and the build plan.
        </p>
        <a href="/digital-context-audit" class="btn btn-primary" data-animate data-animate-delay="0.2">
          Get Your Digital Context Audit &rarr;
        </a>
      </SectionReveal>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="section-sm border-t border-gray-800">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <p class="text-small text-gray-400 mb-6" data-animate-fade>Related Concepts</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-6" data-animate>
        <a href="/physics-of-growth/mass" class="text-white hover:text-accent transition-colors">
          Mass &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="/physics-of-growth/momentum" class="text-white hover:text-accent transition-colors">
          Momentum &rarr;
        </a>
        <a href="/physics-of-growth/surface-area" class="text-white hover:text-accent transition-colors">
          Surface Area &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Newsletter -->
  <NewsletterForm variant="compact" />

</BaseLayout>
